than an entire year's
salary out of this, huh?

62
00:04:01,291 --> 00:04:02,291
Don't bother speculating

63
00:04:02,375 --> 00:04:03,583
on how much you're gonna get.

64
00:04:03,666 --> 00:04:05,666
It'll only bring
you disappointment.

65
00:04:06,125 --> 00:04:08,500
We do the job
we're hired to do...

66
00:04:08,583 --> 00:04:11,458
and that's all you should
concern yourself with.

67
00:04:11,541 --> 00:04:13,875
Somebody! Come quick!

68
00:04:13,958 --> 00:04:15,708
Stay here and watch the girl.

69
00:04:20,375 --> 00:04:21,625
What the--?!

70
00:04:21,708 --> 00:04:23,750
Who could have done this?

71
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:25,166
Well, are they both alive?

72
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:27,666
Yeah. They're just
knocked out pretty good.

73
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:29,625
This is strange.

74
00:04:29,708 --> 00:04:31,166
Huh?

75
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:33,416
Whoever did this could
have just killed them.

76
00:04:33,500 --> 00:04:35,083
Why put them
on display like this?

77
00:04:35,166 --> 00:04:37,666
What purpose does it serve?

78
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:39,458
Oh no it's about the girl!

79
00:04:40,666 --> 00:04:43,000
We're dealing with a pro guys.

80
00:04:43,541 --> 00:04:45,083
Come on. Get up.

81
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:50,250
I had guards placed
all over this floor.

82
00:04:50,333 --> 00:04:51,791
How did he...

83
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:53,375
Sorry, sir.

84
00:04:55,083 --> 00:04:58,000
I never even saw it,
I was attacked from above.

85
00:04:58,083 --> 00:04:59,375
Above?

86
00:05:02,833 --> 00:05:04,708
Oh, I see.

87
00:05:05,875 --> 00:05:07,833
Send out an alert.
Seal all the exits.

88
00:05:07,916 --> 00:05:09,500
We can't let them get away.

89
00:05:09,583 --> 00:05:10,916
Yes, sir!

90
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,333
You three come with me.

91
00:05:12,416 --> 00:05:15,291
We're going on a rat hunt
boys so bring your A game.

92
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:18,250
It's a real ballsy
move to steal a mark

93
00:05:18,333 --> 00:05:20,416
from professional kidnappers...

94
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:24,125
This guy has no idea
who he's dealing with.

95
00:05:24,791 --> 00:05:26,250
That was close.

96
00:05:30,875 --> 00:05:32,291
I recognize that guy.

97
00:05:32,375 --> 00:05:34,083
He's the legendary
Night Mist, the best,

98
00:05:34,166 --> 00:05:36,875
or at least most professional,
kidnapper in the world.

99
00:05:36,958 --> 00:05:40,500
And that guy's quick so
I gotta be one step ahead.

100
00:05:40,583 --> 00:05:42,250
Stop wiggling kid.

101
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:44,875
Kosuna can you
hear me? Kosuna? Pick up!

102
00:05:44,958 --> 00:05:46,291
Yeah. Loud and clear.

103
00:05:46,375 --> 00:05:47,666
The situation has changed.

104
00:05:47,750 --> 00:05:50,375
Switch our strategy from
Cyclone to Hurricane. Copy?

105
00:05:50,458 --> 00:05:53,416
What? I just finished
setting up Cyclone!

106
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:55,875
Stop complaining and just do it!

107
00:05:55,958 --> 00:05:58,083
Fine. Right away sir.

108
00:05:59,250 --> 00:06:01,750
Calm down. It's gonna
be all right kid.

109
00:06:01,833 --> 00:06:03,541
You must have
been pretty scared, huh?

110
00:06:04,875 --> 00:06:06,333
The nerve of
those guys tying up

111
00:06:06,416 --> 00:06:09,333
a helpless child like
this. You poor thing.

112
00:06:09,416 --> 00:06:11,083
You're lucky I
found you in time.

113
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,291
Get away!

114
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:15,250
What's wrong?

115
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:17,375
Mind your own business, pal.

116
00:06:17,458 --> 00:06:18,916
Mind my own what?!

117
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:21,000
I bet my daddy asked
you to rescue me...

118
00:06:21,083 --> 00:06:23,291
Figures he can't do it himself.

119
00:06:23,375 --> 00:06:26,666
Yeah, uh, he hired me.

120
00:06:26,750 --> 00:06:28,083
I hope you're careful with me

121
00:06:28,166 --> 00:06:29,875
because I don't want to
get caught in the crossfire

122
00:06:29,958 --> 00:06:32,375
of a gunfight between
you macho boys.

123
00:06:32,458 --> 00:06:33,916
If my daddy had
just paid the ransom

124
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,125
this would all be over with

125
00:06:35,208 --> 00:06:36,916
and I'd be at home with my toys.

126
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:37,708
But...

127
00:06:37,791 --> 00:06:39,250
Oh no! My favorite dress!

128
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:41,333
Look you got it
all dirtied up...!

129
00:06:41,416 --> 00:06:43,041
What are you going
to do about it, huh?

130
00:06:43,125 --> 00:06:44,500
It was a one of a kind!

131
00:06:44,583 --> 00:06:47,666
What am I going to do
about it, I'm rescuing you?!

132
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:48,833
I assume we're going to have

133
00:06:48,916 --> 00:06:50,291
to start walking
after this right...?

134
00:06:50,375 --> 00:06:51,666
Of course we--

135
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:52,791
Well I'll have you know
that I don't like to walk...

136
00:06:52,875 --> 00:06:54,333
What are you nuts?

137
00:06:54,416 --> 00:06:56,375
And I'm hungry too and I assume
you have some food for me.

138
00:06:56,458 --> 00:06:59,375
You're starting
to drive me crazy!

139
00:06:59,458 --> 00:07:00,250
Don't you know how to listen

140
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:01,500
when someone's talking?!

141
00:07:05,375 --> 00:07:06,833
I would think you'd
act a little nicer

142
00:07:06,916 --> 00:07:08,708
to someone who's
trying to save your life.

143
00:07:08,791 --> 00:07:10,125
But what do I know?

144
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:13,875
Look little girl.

145
00:07:13,958 --> 00:07:15,875
This is not a simple
snatch-and-grab kidnap

146
00:07:15,958 --> 00:07:17,250
for ransom case okay?

147
00:07:17,333 --> 00:07:18,666
There's a lot
more to it than that.

148
00:07:18,750 --> 00:07:20,500
What are you talking about?

149
00:07:20,583 --> 00:07:22,000
These guys are professionals

150
00:07:22,083 --> 00:07:23,333
that were hired to kidnap you.

151
00:07:23,416 --> 00:07:25,750
They're not thugs
looking for a quick buck.

152
00:07:25,833 --> 00:07:27,125
But I don't understand.

153
00:07:27,208 --> 00:07:29,833
I'm just an innocent,
fragile, little girl.

154
00:07:30,791 --> 00:07:31,916
Okay.

155
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,666
Your father recently
used some, questionable

156
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:36,166
if not unethical, tactics
to aid in the demise

157
00:07:36,250 --> 00:07:38,375
of a rival company. Got it?

158
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:39,958
Now the person
that hired these guys

159
00:07:40,041 --> 00:07:42,541
to kidnap you is probably
the owner of that company.

160
00:07:42,625 --> 00:07:44,583
Um, whatever you say.

161
00:07:44,666 --> 00:07:46,625
In other words their
goal is not money.

162
00:07:46,708 --> 00:07:48,250
It's a grudge. It's malice.

163
00:07:48,333 --> 00:07:49,958
Their goal is to
make your father suffer

164
00:07:50,041 --> 00:07:51,208
in the worst possible way,

165
00:07:51,291 --> 00:07:53,458
which is why you're here now.

166
00:07:54,916 --> 00:07:57,125
Geez! You just don't
get it do you?!

167
00:07:57,208 --> 00:07:59,125
Listen to me. Okay?

168
00:07:59,208 --> 00:08:00,625
What I'm saying
is paying the ransom

169
00:08:00,708 --> 00:08:04,000
doesn't mean you're going
to go home safe and sound.

170
00:08:04,083 --> 00:08:05,750
Is, that a fact?

171
00:08:05,833 --> 00:08:08,083
Yes. Usually they
would just take the ransom

172
00:08:08,166 --> 00:08:09,458
and then kill you anyway.

173
00:08:11,250 --> 00:08:13,000
You get off lucky
if they just kill you.

174
00:08:13,083 --> 00:08:14,333
However more often than not,

175
00:08:14,416 --> 00:08:16,500
they'll force you to
satisfy the desires of fat,

176
00:08:16,583 --> 00:08:20,250
sweaty, stanked-out men
and trust me little girl,

177
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:23,375
death is a sweet
release in comparison.

178
00:08:25,916 --> 00:08:26,916
I got her scared.

179
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,958
Good, that should
keep her in line.

180
00:08:29,041 --> 00:08:30,125
Would the fat man want me

181
00:08:30,208 --> 00:08:32,041
because he thinks I'm cute?

182
00:08:33,041 --> 00:08:34,083
I knew it...

183
00:08:34,166 --> 00:08:35,583
I know I shouldn't
point it out myself,

184
00:08:35,666 --> 00:08:37,541
but I'm a pretty girl
that all the boys want

185
00:08:37,625 --> 00:08:38,916
to be with, aren't I?!

186
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,916
Give me a break.

187
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:43,625
It must be because I've
been raised so well...

188
00:08:43,708 --> 00:08:45,416
Even criminals can see it...

189
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:48,541
I'll grow up to be a great
wife and an excellent mother.

190
00:08:48,625 --> 00:08:50,875
I don't believe
this wretched kid!

191
00:08:50,958 --> 00:08:52,291
Look we have
to start running now

192
00:08:52,375 --> 00:08:54,666
or we'll be throat
deep in trouble! Got it?

193
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:57,458
Sure I got it but,
my conditions are no pain,

194
00:08:57,541 --> 00:08:59,833
no dirt, and no
running. Got that?

195
00:09:01,166 --> 00:09:03,333
Why did I take this job?

196
00:09:07,583 --> 00:09:08,833
Time to go. They found us.

197
00:09:08,916 --> 00:09:10,000
They did?

198
00:09:11,166 --> 00:09:12,541
Shut up and run.
We have to move!

199
00:09:12,625 --> 00:09:13,500
Hold on!

200
00:09:14,083 --> 00:09:15,166
I don't think it's on... hey!

201
00:09:15,250 --> 00:09:17,708
We found them. Thirteenth
floor section B.

202
00:09:17,791 --> 00:09:20,583
Okay let everyone know
we're closing in on the rat.

203
00:09:20,666 --> 00:09:22,041
Stay focused out there.

204
00:09:22,125 --> 00:09:23,375
Copy that.

205
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,875
Huh, this is
starting to get fun...

206
00:09:26,958 --> 00:09:29,916
It's been awhile since
I've felt such a rush.

207
00:09:48,166 --> 00:09:49,125
Impressive.

208
00:09:49,208 --> 00:09:50,916
They're approaching
on all sides.

209
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:54,416
Waiting patiently, no rushing,
slowly closing in on us.

210
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:56,125
Hey.

211
00:09:56,208 --> 00:09:57,625
There's no hesitation.

212
00:09:57,708 --> 00:09:59,125
Hello!

213
00:09:59,208 --> 00:10:01,416
They must know this
building inside and out.

214
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:02,791
Mister!

215
00:10:02,875 --> 00:10:04,125
This isn't going to be easy.

216
00:10:04,208 --> 00:10:07,041
They have a solid
advantage from every position.

217
00:10:07,125 --> 00:10:08,625
Listen to me!

218
00:10:08,708 --> 00:10:10,000
What is it?!

219
00:10:10,083 --> 00:10:12,416
I'm really tired.

220
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:15,958
Tired? We haven't even
walked five minutes yet.

221
00:10:16,041 --> 00:10:18,916
I can't take another step.

222
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,875
Come on kid. Enough
with the games already.

223
00:10:24,166 --> 00:10:25,000
Shut up kid!

224
00:10:25,083 --> 00:10:27,000
You'll give away our position!

225
00:10:29,041 --> 00:10:30,041
I'm dirty and I'm hungry.

226
00:10:30,125 --> 00:10:31,541
She's gonna blow
this whole operation!

227
00:10:31,625 --> 00:10:33,583
I want to go home
and see my daddy!

228
00:10:33,666 --> 00:10:35,916
I'd give anything for a
tranquilizer dart right now

229
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:40,041
but even then my exits
are all blocked... Kosuna.

230
00:10:40,458 --> 00:10:41,333
Do you read me?

231
00:10:41,416 --> 00:10:42,166
Yes, Master.

232
00:10:42,250 --> 00:10:43,625
I read you.

233
00:10:45,833 --> 00:10:47,291
What's going on?

234
00:10:47,375 --> 00:10:48,708
Well I can honestly say that

235
00:10:48,791 --> 00:10:50,666
since we teamed up
this is the first time

236
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:53,333
I've found you to
be an obedient kid.

237
00:10:53,416 --> 00:10:54,833
Okay...?

238
00:10:54,916 --> 00:10:57,250
Anyways I need you to
drop the Hurricane strategy.

239
00:10:57,333 --> 00:10:58,916
We're moving right
into Monsoon now.

240
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:00,458
We're changing again?

241
00:11:00,541 --> 00:11:02,125
I was almost finished!

242
00:11:02,208 --> 00:11:03,291
I don't care!

243
00:11:03,375 --> 00:11:04,708
You have to be
ready to change strategies

244
00:11:04,791 --> 00:11:07,291
at a moment's notice
depending on the situation.

245
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:08,375
Now go!

246
00:11:11,375 --> 00:11:13,666
Come on kid let's get moving...

247
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:15,000
Hello?

248
00:11:16,291 --> 00:11:17,500
What is it?

249
00:11:17,583 --> 00:11:18,625
You're not going to
throw another fit are you?

250
00:11:19,625 --> 00:11:21,916
I have to use the facilities.

251
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,041
What?

252
00:11:23,125 --> 00:11:25,625
I have to use the facilities.

253
00:11:25,708 --> 00:11:28,166
Speak up kid.

254
00:11:28,250 --> 00:11:30,416
I said, I need to...

255
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:33,125
Volume! I can't hear a word.

256
00:11:33,208 --> 00:11:35,291
Stop trying to
embarrass me you ass!

257
00:11:35,375 --> 00:11:38,291
I have to pee real bad!
That's what I was saying!

258
00:11:38,375 --> 00:11:39,625
Oh, you have to pee.

